1 Section 1. Chapter 201 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto the provisions set forth as sections 2 and 3 of this act.
3 Sec. 2. The Legislature hereby declares that the public policy
4 of this State is to encourage victims and witnesses of serious
5 violent crimes to report such crimes and to participate in the
6 criminal justice system. Those persons who are working in sex
7 industries that are criminalized by state law often do not report
8 serious crimes committed against themselves, or committed
9 against others in their presence, because of fear of arrest and
10 prosecution for sex work and low-level drug crimes. Providing
11 immunity from criminal liability to persons engaging in
12 prostitution or committing certain acts while engaged in
13 prostitution ensures that victims and witnesses of serious violent
14 crimes that occur during prostitution offenses may come forward
15 to report the perpetrators without fear of arrest and prosecution.
16 Sec. 3. 1. Notwithstanding any other provision of law, a
17 person described in subsection 2 is immune from criminal liability
18 for committing:
19 (a) A violation of any provision of NRS 201.353 or 207.030
20 relating to prostitution;
21 (b) A violation of Chapter 453 of NRS relating to:
22 (1) Drug paraphernalia, including, without limitation, NRS
23 453.554 to 453.566, inclusive;
24 (2) Possession, unless it is for the purpose of sale or
25 violates the provisions of NRS 453.3385, subsection 2 of NRS
26 453.3393 or 453.3405; or
27 (3) Use of a controlled substance, including, without
28 limitation, NRS 453.336; or
29 (c) Any of the following offenses:
30 (1) Obstructing a public officer pursuant to NRS 197.190;
31 (2) Breaching the peace pursuant to NRS 203.010;
32 (3) Loitering or any act of vagrancy pursuant to
33 NRS 207.030;
34 (4) Trespass pursuant to NRS 207.200; or
35 (5) Any similar offense punishable by a county, city or town
36 ordinance.
37 2. A person qualifies for the immunity provided pursuant to
38 subsection 1 if the person commits any of the offenses described in
39 subsection 1 during the course of allegedly engaging in
40 prostitution and:
41 (a) Is a victim of or witness to any of the following offenses:
42 (1) Human trafficking as defined in NRS 49.25425;
